div.p:
He was an afflicted King. Some would have this expreſſed in the Text: I will praiſe thee: for thou haſt afflicted me. The Original word will bear both Interpretations;

                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉


               Thou haſt afflicted me, or, Thou haſt anſwered me. But however, his afflicted condition is implyed enough in the news we have in the Text of the return which God had made unto his prayers.
